President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. William P. Doyle is nominated for Commissioner of the Federal Maritime Commission. Richard A. Lidinsky, Jr. is nominated for Chairman of the Federal Maritime Commission. James M. Demers is nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. Naomi A. Walker is nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. Katrina McFarland is nominated for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Acquisition at the Department of Defense. Kenneth Merten is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Croatia at the Department of State. Additionally, President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts, including David Kotelchuck, Loretta R. Valerio, Karen L. Jefferson, Martin C. Faga, and William H. Leary. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future.